com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.read

Enum ReaderType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ReaderType>
      • com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.read.ReaderType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ReaderType>

    public enum ReaderType
extends java.lang.Enum<ReaderType>
    The ReaderType enum is used to hold information about all known TableReader classes. This information includes what class the enum constant maps to, as well as what file extensions it is (usually) appropriate to use the table reader type with.

      • getReaderTypeFromExtension

        public static ReaderType getReaderTypeFromExtension(java.lang.String fileExtension)
        Infer the appropriate reader type to use with the specified file extension. This method checks to see if the extension exists in any of the ReaderType's commonly used file types, and return the type that can use the file type. If no reader is found which is known to work with the file type, null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        fileExtension - The file extension in question.
        Returns:
        the reader type which was deemed appropriate for use with fileExtension, or null if none was found.

      • getReaderType

        public static ReaderType getReaderType(java.lang.String filePath)
        Infer the appropriate reader type to use with the specified file. The ReaderType class holds a list of possible file extensions mapping to each ReaderType, and this mapping is used by this method to determine the reader type to use.
        Parameters:
        filePath - The path to the data file; this must have an extension, as this is used to determine the reader type.
        Returns:
        the reader type which was deemed appropriate for use with file.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a file extension was not found.
        TableDataException - if no known mapping from file's extension to a table reader type is known.
